"Abstract After promising for a number of years to enact an Information Practices Act, the Government of Malta has finally, in May 2000, published a “White Paper on the Legislative Framework for Information Practices” 2 . This document was open for comment from the public until the end of June and it is expected that the draft Bills contained in the White Paper, after having been appropriately amended following the public comments, will be presented before the Maltese Parliament in Autumn 2000. This note examines the proposals currently under consideration."
